<TITLE> Court halts Hasina hearing until Tuesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 6 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Sunday set a new date for the indictment hearing on former prime minister Sheikh Hasina as she was ill. Metropolitan sessions judge Azizul Haque will hear the extortion charges against Hasina Tuesday. Hasina fell sick in court on Dec 31 soon after the hearing took off in the makeshift courtroom of the sessions judge on the Jatiya Sangsad premises. The Awami League chief is facing charges of taking cash from the managing director of Eastcoast Trading, Azam Jahangir Chowdhury, who filed an extortion case against her in June. bd
